Genre Music Tree

Claudia Soto

13/7/2020

Description

Using a dataset comprised of songs of two music genres (Hip-Hop and Rock), you will train a classifier to distinguish between the two genres based only on track information derived from Echonest (now part of Spotify).

Streaming services have looked into means of categorizing music to allow for personalized recommendations. One method involves direct analysis of the raw audio information in a given song, scoring the raw data on a variety of metrics.

Lets load the metadata about our tracks alongside the track metrics compiled by The Echo Nest. A song is about more than its title, artist, and number of listens. We have another dataset that has musical features of each track such as danceability and acousticness on a scale from -1 to 1.

For more information Song Genre Classification from Audio Data using ML.

#split
set.seed(1)
train_index = sample(1:length(echo_track$genre_top), length(echo_track$genre_top)*.80)
model_tree <-
  decision_tree() %>%
  set_engine("rpart") %>%
  set_mode("classification") %>% 
  translate()
model_tree
## Decision Tree Model Specification (classification)
## 
## Computational engine: rpart 
## 
## Model fit template:
## rpart::rpart(formula = missing_arg(), data = missing_arg(), weights = missing_arg())
tree.music <- model_tree %>% 
  fit(factor(genre_top) ~., data = echo_track %>% select(-track_id))
